Package io.guldbrand.unit

Class U

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.guldbrand.unit.U

  • public class U
extends Object
    Compound Unit, a unit with one or more quantities.

    Class and methods primarily for defining, calculating and converting between units of basic and compounded quantities.

    Some additional functionality exists for doing absolute conversion between scales, as well as units such as months and years. Those do however have limited functionality. This code should not be used to implement calendar systems.

    • Constructor Detail

      • U

        public U​(String shortName,
         String longName,
         Quantity quantity)
        Creates a new Unit from scratch. If there already exists a Unit that you want to base a new one on, use U(io.guldbrand.unit.U,double,java.lang.String,java.lang.String) instead.}
        Parameters:
        shortName - the short name or abbreviation for this unit. For the SI-unit meter this would be "m".
        longName - the long name for this unit. For the SI-unit meter this would be "meter".
        quantity - the quantity that this unit will represent.

      • U

        public U​(U u,
         double compoundLength,
         String shortName,
         String longName)
        Defines a new Unit based on another. The new unit will have the same Quantity as the old one but can be given a different length and name.
        Parameters:
        u - the Unit this unit will have the same quantity as.
        compoundLength - the length of this unit compared to the other Unit. For the SI-unit millimeter this would be 0.001 if the other Unit was meter.
        shortName - the short name or abbreviation for this unit. For the SI-unit meter this would be "m".
        longName - the long name for this unit. For the SI-unit meter this would be "meter".

      • inverse

        public U inverse​()
        Calculate the inverse of this unit. This is equivalent to pow(-1).
        Returns:
        The resulting inverted unit.

      • reduce

        public U reduce​()
        Checks the unit for multiple instances of the same quantity and combines them. This will for instance convert ( m^2 / m ) to ( m ).
        Returns:
        the reduced compound unit.

      • dimDiff

        public U dimDiff​(U b)
        Calculates and the Unit that is the dimensional difference between this Unit and another. That will be the unit you should multiply this unit with to get the target unit. Ex: meter.dimDiff( kg ) will return the unit ( kg / m ).
        Parameters:
        b - the target Unit.
        Returns:
        a Unit representing the dimensional difference between this and target unit.

      • dimDiff

        public static U dimDiff​(U a,
                        U b)
        Calculates and the Unit that is the dimensional difference between Unit A and Unit B. That will be the unit you should multiply A with to get B. Ex: dimDiff( meter, kg ) will return the unit ( kg / m ).
        Parameters:
        a - the unit that can be multiplied with returned value to get B.
        b - the other unit.
        Returns:
        a Unit representing the dimensional difference between this and target unit.

      • isSameQuantity

        public boolean isSameQuantity​(U b)
        Checks whether or not this unit and unit b has the same total quantity. (Basically if they could be added.)
        Parameters:
        b - the unit to check against.
        Returns:
        True iff the units have the same quantity.
